Here's how to handle each scenario with modern MSTest (3.9+):

```csharp
[TestClass]
public sealed class AdvancedConditionTests : IDisposable
{
    private readonly string _tempFile;

    public AdvancedConditionTests()
    {
        // Temp file created in constructor
        _tempFile = Path.GetTempFileName();
    }

    // 1. Windows-only (registry access)
    [TestMethod]
    [OSCondition(OperatingSystems.Windows)]
    public void Registry_ReadsInstallPath()
    {
        var value = Registry.GetValue(@"HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\MyApp", "InstallDir", null);
        Assert.IsNotNull(value);
    }

    // 2. Skip in CI (requires local GPU)
    [TestMethod]
    [CICondition(ConditionMode.Exclude)]
    public void RenderFrame_UsesLocalGpu()
    {
        var result = GpuRenderer.RenderTestFrame();
        Assert.IsTrue(result.Success);
    }

    // 3. Flaky external API — retry up to 3 times
    [TestMethod]
    [Retry(3)]
    [Timeout(10000)]
    public async Task WeatherApi_ReturnsForecast(TestContext testContext)
    {
        var forecast = await _weatherClient.GetForecastAsync(testContext.CancellationToken);
        Assert.IsNotNull(forecast);
    }

    // 4. Cleanup runs even if test fails (via IDisposable or [TestCleanup])
    [TestCleanup]
    public void Cleanup()
    {
        if (File.Exists(_tempFile))
        {
            File.Delete(_tempFile);
        }
    }

    // Alternative: IDisposable also works for cleanup
    public void Dispose()
    {
        // Runs after TestCleanup
    }
}
```

**Summary of attributes:**

| Scenario | Attribute | MSTest version |
|----------|-----------|----------------|
| OS-specific | `[OSCondition(OperatingSystems.Windows)]` | 3.10+ |
| Skip in CI | `[CICondition(ConditionMode.Exclude)]` | 3.10+ |
| Flaky retry | `[Retry(3)]` | 3.9+ |
| Guaranteed cleanup | `[TestCleanup]` or `IDisposable` | All |

**Key notes:**
- `[TestCleanup]` and `Dispose` run even when a test fails — use them for file/resource cleanup.
- `[Retry]` should only be used for genuinely flaky external dependencies, not to mask bugs.
- Combine `[Timeout]` with `TestContext.CancellationToken` for cooperative cancellation on retried async tests.
